Sentencas: In this paper, a model of a complete structured methane (CH4) internal reforming solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) stack is developed.
Titulo: Transient thermomechanical analysis of a 1 kW solid oxide fuel cell stack based on 3D multiphysical field model

Sentencas: Material properties are extracted from experiments to establish a numerical simulation model to elucidate the mechanical failure mechanism of the stack under the combined effect of multiple factors.
Titulo: Transient thermomechanical analysis of a 1 kW solid oxide fuel cell stack based on 3D multiphysical field model

Sentencas: The steady-state and transient temperature and stress distributions of the stack are investigated.
Titulo: Transient thermomechanical analysis of a 1 kW solid oxide fuel cell stack based on 3D multiphysical field model

Sentencas: Results show that the higher the number of stacked layers, the more inhomogeneous the temperature distribution, the lower the fuel and oxygen (O-2) utilization and potential of the cell, and the reduced flow rate in the top layer.
Titulo: Transient thermomechanical analysis of a 1 kW solid oxide fuel cell stack based on 3D multiphysical field model

Sentencas: The maximum temperature difference decreases rapidly during the first 50 mins of the stack shutdown.
Titulo: Transient thermomechanical analysis of a 1 kW solid oxide fuel cell stack based on 3D multiphysical field model

Sentencas: The first principal stress at the anode of the co-flow stack first decreases in the first few minutes of shutdown, then increases rapidly and is higher than the value at time 0.
Titulo: Transient thermomechanical analysis of a 1 kW solid oxide fuel cell stack based on 3D multiphysical field model

Sentencas: The first principal stress in the anode of the counterflow stack first increases and then decreases, with an increase of about 100 MPa.
Titulo: Transient thermomechanical analysis of a 1 kW solid oxide fuel cell stack based on 3D multiphysical field model

Sentencas: The maximum first principal stresses of the electrolyte and cathode decrease nearly monotonically, and the first principal stresses are smaller than the steady-state values.
Titulo: Transient thermomechanical analysis of a 1 kW solid oxide fuel cell stack based on 3D multiphysical field model
